The only warriors i've ever ever ever seen have problems taunting were either a) low level for the group, b) woe-fully underequipped for weapons (like using a lammy at 5<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> , or c) incompetant and didn't understand proximity's effect on aggro.  In a single group I have *never* had problems taunting.  At level 52 using a total junk weapon (sword breaker) I was able to taunt chef in sebilis just fine even with a 60 ranger in group with his epics and a 55 monk with epics.  The only time you have trouble taunting is when you don't know how to control aggro...that's a bad player NOT the class.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
Warriors are not needed in groups<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Not needed but better than any alternative for tanking.  Its not possible to argue with this.  Warriors are equal or better in EVERY possible thing you can look at for tanking.  Its not even close.<br>
 <p>Gorlab 59 Warrior<BR>
Tenakha 52 Druid<BR>
